Kotri, a fox girl who likes to dance. Her hair color changes according to the magic she is performaing.
She's been practicing magic with Pandora a lot. Fire element is one of her best tricks up her sleeves, and thus her hair color is usually red/pink-ish.
Maybe if she master all the elemental magic, she could become rainbow-colored Kotri?

She had mixed feelings when she found out that Irisu is a rabbit.
It wasn't because her friend Irisu was hiding the truth from her.
It's because Kotri realized that she was looking at Irisu differently: Kotri is a fox and Irisu is a rabbit. Kotri is afraid that one day she might become a member of the UPRPRC...

If you see Ashuri gazing at something in a strange way, it's likely because she's eagerly want to study it, so be sure to keep an eye on her and her curiosity...
Despite this, she's genuinely kind and a reliable older sister most of the time.

She recently met Syaro on the road, who is on the way home from grocery.
Syaro and Cicini always stay together. It is quite unusual to see Syaro alone.
When Ashuri talks to her, Syaro seems uncanny. Maybe it's because Syaro is from "the outside world"? Or Syaro is just being a polite person and maybe a little bit too serious?

Anyway, Ashuri personally feel that Syaro might see her as a werido, and she was quite sad about it.

A very upbeat litt-... great fairy, Ribbon!
Her wish is to become human-sized and live a human life with Erina.
She lives with Erina, Rumi, and Miru under the same roof (and sometimes Cocoa, Pixie, and Lily).

After Ribbon resolving the crisis of Rabi Rabi Island with Erina, she become a renowned member of fairies and is respected and loved by her kinds. She was even invited back to the forest by the High Fairies.
Ribbon paid a short visit to the forest once, but only to escape from there again: She cannot stand the way that she was treated and cared for like a princess.

Rumi is troubled by the relationship between she and her little sister Miru, which she usually feel apart from her.
The fact that Miru actually likes to be with Rumi, but she find it hard to express due to her introvert personality.
Also Miru prefers to stay with Erina, who by her nature is a rabbit rather than a human. Don't bring it up in front of Rumi.

Rumour goes that she's been working with Miriam, Pandora and Ashuri on a potion that can turn them into rabbits.
People are afraid to go near Miriam's shop at night because of strange noises and flashes coming out from the windows.
What's the purpose of their research?!

Seana, a girl who lives in the Nature Aquarium.
She's a dangerous idol due to her voice carry the offensice magic that can actually harm people, but it seems she doesn't aware about that.

Her recent duet concert with Aruraune went very well.
She is quite surprise about the good experience when singing in the forest, and is thinking about inviting Lilith and hold a trio concent next time.
Although people have to surround the stage with magical barriers in order to keep the audience safe.

Saya, a girl who lives on the Evernight Peak by herself. 
Though it's hard to tell from her appearance, she's actually one of the most powerful magic user on Rabi Rabi Island.
She even mastered magic of wind element lately, which give her the control of winds among the island, so it's basicaly sunny day almost every day on Rabi Rabi Island.

Recently, her senpai, Rita, has been able to notice her presence on a regular basis, which makes Saya very happy, even too happy for her to sleep when she thinks about that.
Lacking sleep lead to the challenge of waking up in the morning, and thus being late to wake up Rita senpai, who also always waking up late.

Let's hope she can get back to the regular sleeping schedule soon!
